1.1 – Introduction to JavaScript

JavaScript is a high-level, dynamic programming language used to make web pages interactive.
It was created by Brendan Eich in 1995 and today runs both in the browser and on servers (Node.js).

Key Points:

Runs through engines like V8 (Chrome) and SpiderMonkey (Firefox).

Supports multiple styles: object-oriented, functional, imperative.

Controls dynamic behavior such as UI updates, animations, events, API calls etc.
